essin as the ligand. Hydroxy[Thr4,Gly7]oxytocin, a selective oxytocin agonist (20), was added to the incubation medium to reduce binding of [3H]vasopressin to oxytocin receptors. To assess the amount of nonspecific labeling, adjacent sections were treated in the same conditions, except that the incubation medium contained in addition 10 AM nonradioactive vasopressin. To determine whether the va-sopressin-binding sites were of the V1-or V2-type, competition experiments were performed on sections containing the ventral hypothalamus. The incubation medium was then supplemented with 150 nM [Phe2,Orn8]vasotocin, a VI (va-sopressor type) receptor agonist in which Om = ornithine, or 1-deamino-[D-Arg8]vasopressin (dDAVP), a peptide selective for V2 (antidiuretic type) receptors (20). Oxytocin-binding sites were detected by using as ligand 0.05 nM 125I-labeled 8-ornithine/9-tyrosinamide-containing vasotocin (125I-OTAVT) designated 1-deamino-[Cys(CH2)A, Tyr(Me)2, Thr4, Orn8, Tyr9-NH2]vasotocin in-which Cys-1 has been deaminated and substituted on the side chain with cyclopentamethylene to form [1-(3-mercapto-34,-cyclopen-tamethylenepropionic acid), 2-O-methyltyrosine, 4-threo-nine, 8-ornithine, 9-tyrosinamide]vasotocin. This compound has also been called d(CH2)5[Tyr(Me)2,ThrJTyr(NH2)91orni-Abbreviations: Orn, ornithine; OTAVT, 8-ornithine/9-tyrosinamide-containing vasotocin designated 1-deamino-[Cys(CH2)1, Tyr(Me)2, Thr4, Orn8, Tyr9-NH2]vasotocin in which Cys-1 has been deaminated and substituted on the 1-carbon with cyclopentamethylene to form [1-1-mercapto-f,13-cyclopentamethylenepropionic acid, 2-0-methyltyrosine, 4-threonine, 8-ornithine, 9-tyrosinamide]vasotocin. tTo whom reprint requests should be addressed. 11163 The publication costs of this article were defrayed in part by page charge payment. This article must therefore be hereby marked "advertisement" in accordance with 18 U.S.C. {\S}1734 solely to indicate this fact.},
